.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36F6FFEF9D20FF0BFAC5F268FA3A" blockId="27.[151,1286,1405,1429]" box="[151,1286,1405,1429]" pageId="27" pageNumber="46">
This species is related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D75FFEF9D20FE38FAC6F5EDFA3B" box="[420,643,1406,1429]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrciaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomerata">
<emphasis id="B914EAE4FFEF9D20FE38FAC6F5EDFA3B" box="[420,643,1406,1429]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="46">Myrciaria glomerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing through its glabrous and longly acuminate leaves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36F6FFEF9D26FF0BFA06F58FFF79" blockId="27.[151,1436,1470,2037]" lastBlockId="29.[151,1436,152,820]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="27" pageNumber="46">
Tree (?). Twigs grey, glabrous or with scattered simple grey or white trichomes to 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FB18FA06F38DFA76" box="[1156,1251,1470,1496]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
, the internodes 15–25 × 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FE9EFA5CF611FA50" box="[258,383,1508,1534]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
. Leaves with petioles glabrous or with trichomes as the twigs, canaliculate, 5–7 × 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FAC5FA5CF7A7F98B" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="1.1" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="1.0">1–1.2 mm</quantity>
; blades elliptic–caudate, 65–90 × 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FDFBF9B3F582F98B" box="[615,748,1547,1573]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="29.0" valueMax="33.0" valueMin="25.0">25–33 mm</quantity>
, 2.6–3.3 times longer than wide, concoloured or slightly discoloured when dried, glabrous or with scattered simple trichomes 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FC70F98AF306F9E2" box="[1004,1128,1586,1612]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
along the midvein at the abaxial side; glandular dots visible only against light, smaller than 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FC53F9E0F345F9DC" box="[975,1067,1624,1650]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
in diameter and about ten per square milimeter; apex caudate and mucronate in 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FD69F9C7F414F937" box="[757,890,1663,1689]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="16.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="13.0">13–20 mm</quantity>
; base cuneate; midvein sulcate adaxially and prominent abaxially; secondary veins 12 to 30 at each side, straight, leaving the midvein at angles about 70 degrees, weakly prominent adaxially and a little more so abaxially; marginal vein to 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FBEAF974F3BEF948" box="[1142,1232,1740,1766]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
from the margin, the margin itself with a yellow thickening to 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FD2BF94BF47CF8A3" box="[695,786,1779,1805]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
wide. Inflorescences glomerulate, axillary, with up to four sessile flowers; bracteoles fused at least when young, elliptic, to 2.7 × 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FB94F8A2F320F89A" box="[1032,1102,1818,1844]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
, darker than the flower buds when dry, somewhat covered with grey trichomes to 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FC9BF8F8F40BF8F4" box="[775,869,1856,1882]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
; flower buds obovate, 5–6 × 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FB21F8F8F26BF8F4" box="[1213,1285,1856,1882]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, densely and uniformly covered with grey to white trichomes to 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FD6EF8DFF457F82F" box="[754,825,1895,1921]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
; calyx lobes four, more or less equal between them, ovate, 2 × 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FE84F836F6FBF806" box="[280,405,1934,1960]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="1.8" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.6">1.6–2 mm</quantity>
, pilose abaxially and glabrous adaxially; petals obovate, 2–2.5 × 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FB37F836F246F806" box="[1195,1320,1934,1960]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="1.9" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.8">1.8–2 mm</quantity>
, glabrous adaxially and moderately covered with brown or grey trichomes 0.2–0.3 abaxially; stamens about 100, to 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FA11F80CF7ABF85B" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
long, the anthers elliptic, 0.2–0.4 × 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FDE5F863F5B9F85B" box="[633,727,2011,2037]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
, eglandular; staminal ring to 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D20FBAAF863F314F85B" box="[1078,1146,2011,2037]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
wide; calyx tube 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFEF9D26FACCF863F7ABFF1C" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="48" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
deep, glabrous; style 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFE99D26FE5BFF20F542FF1C" box="[455,556,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="29" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
, glabrous, the stigma punctiform and not visibly papillose; ovary with two locules and two ovules per locule. Fruits not seen.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1F667EFFE89D27FF0BF865F38CF85C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5060794" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5060794" box="[151,1250,2013,2034]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5060794/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="47" startId="28.[151,244,2013,2034]" targetBox="[151,1434,191,1987]" targetPageId="28">
<paragraph id="8BDF36F6FFE89D27FF0BF865F38CF85C" blockId="28.[151,1250,2013,2034]" box="[151,1250,2013,2034]" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B914EAE4FFE89D27FF0BF865F676F85C" bold="true" box="[151,280,2013,2034]" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">FIGURE 14.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C604D75FFE89D27FE82F865F6B0F85C" authorityName="Sobral" authorityYear="2012" box="[286,478,2013,2034]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrciaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="28" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alagoana">
<emphasis id="B914EAE4FFE89D27FE82F865F6B0F85C" box="[286,478,2013,2034]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="47">Myrciaria alagoana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
— image of holotype (scale — 50 mm). Insert: inflorescence (scale — 10 mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BDF36F6FFE99D26FF5AFF5BF6E2FEE6" blockId="29.[151,1436,152,820]" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">
Distribution, habitat, phenology — this species is known only from two collections gathered in 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFE99D26FADDFF5BF2F2FF53" box="[1345,1436,227,253]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.99872" pageId="29" pageNumber="48" unit="in" value="1968.0">1968 in</quantity>
São Miguel dos Campos, in the northeastern coastal zone of the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49A4F814FFE99D26FC64FEB1F333FE8D" box="[1016,1117,265,291]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">Alagoas</collectingRegion>
. Flowers were collected in April and December.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36F6FFE99D26FF5AFEECF7B5FD82" blockId="29.[151,1436,152,820]" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">
Conservation status — there are about 1200 collections from São Miguel dos Campos (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B07FFE99D26FB7BFEECF216FEC0" author="CRIA &amp; Centro de Referencia &amp; Informacao Ambiental" box="[1255,1400,340,366]" pageId="29" pageNumber="48" refId="ref15776" refString="CRIA (Centro de Referencia em Informacao Ambiental) (2012). specieslink (http: // www. splink. org. br / index). Accessed 2012 - 02 - 19." type="url" year="2012">CRIA 2012</bibRefCitation>
), a municipality of 
<quantity id="4C989B13FFE99D26FEC8FEC4F6C0FE38" box="[340,430,380,406]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="29" pageNumber="48" unit="km" value="360.0">360 km</quantity>
<superScript id="7C159BBEFFE99D26FE32FEC1F6D8FE29" attach="left" box="[430,438,377,391]" fontSize="6" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">2</superScript>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B07FFE99D26FE5BFEC4F53AFE38" author="IBGE &amp; Instituto Brasileiro de Geografia" box="[455,596,380,406]" pageId="29" pageNumber="48" refId="ref16025" refString="IBGE (Instituto Brasileiro de Geografia e Estatistica). (2012) IBGE Cidades @. (http: // www. ibge. gov. br / cidadesat / default. php). Accessed 2012 - 02 - 19." type="url" year="2012">IBGE 2012</bibRefCitation>
), rendering an average of about 3 collections / km 
<superScript id="7C159BBEFFE99D26FB35FEC1F3DFFE29" attach="right" box="[1193,1201,377,391]" fontSize="6" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">2</superScript>
; nevertheless, most of these collections are from more than thirty years ago and present information about the collection sites is wanting; so, although the two known collections of 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D75FFE99D26FC85FE7FF367FE4F" authorityName="Sobral" authorityYear="2012" box="[793,1033,455,481]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrciaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="29" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alagoana">Myrciaria alagoana</taxonomicName>
, as well as the absence of recent collections, may suggest its rarity, it must be scored as DD (Data Deficient) according to IUCN criteria (IUCN 2001)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36F6FFE99D26FF5AFD80F6A9FD33" blockId="29.[151,1436,152,820]" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">
Affinities — 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D75FFE99D26FEF8FD81F53FFDFC" authorityName="Sobral" authorityYear="2012" box="[356,593,569,594]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrciaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="29" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alagoana">
<emphasis id="B914EAE4FFE99D26FEF8FD81F53FFDFC" box="[356,593,569,594]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">Myrciaria alagoana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is apparently related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D75FFE99D26FCECFD81F300FDFC" authority="O. Berg" authorityName="O. Berg" box="[880,1134,568,594]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrciaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="29" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomerata">
<emphasis id="B914EAE4FFE99D26FCECFD81F37EFDFC" box="[880,1040,569,594]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">M. glomerata</emphasis>
O.Berg
</taxonomicName>
(for description see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B07FFE99D26FAFFFD80F7B8FDD6" author="Berg, O. C." pageId="29" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 656" refId="ref15613" refString="Berg, O. C. (1857 - 1859) Myrtaceae. In Martius, K. F. P. von (org.) Flora Brasiliensis 14 (1): 1 - 656." type="journal article" year="1857">Berg 1857</bibRefCitation>
–1859: 365 or 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF14B07FFE99D26FE13FDE6F468FDD6" author="Morais, P. O. &amp; Lombardi, J. A." box="[399,774,606,632]" pageId="29" pageNumber="48" pagination="3 - 32" refId="ref16460" refString="Morais, P. O. &amp; Lombardi, J. A. (2006). A familia Myrtaceae na Reserva Particular do Patrimonio Natural da Serra do Caraca, Catas Altas, Minas Gerais, Brasil. Lundiana 7: 3 - 32." type="journal article" year="2006">Morais &amp; Lombardi 2006: 26</bibRefCitation>
), differing from it through the longly acuminate and abaxially glabrous leaves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36F6FFE99D26FF5AFD11F413FD6D" blockId="29.[151,1436,152,820]" box="[198,893,681,707]" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">Etymology — the epithet is allusive to the collection place.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36F6FFE99D26FF5AFD77F48DFD47" blockId="29.[151,1436,152,820]" box="[198,995,719,745]" pageId="29" pageNumber="48">
